  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Network Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description – Network & Security Engineer</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide day-to-day operations and administration support for network and security infrastructure in line with agreed Service Level Agreements (SLAs).</p></li><li><p>Monitor, maintain, and troubleshoot network devices to ensure high availability, performance, and security.</p></li><li><p>Configure, manage, and support routers and switches, primarily Cisco-based environments.</p></li><li><p>Perform incident resolution, root cause analysis, and implement preventive measures.</p></li><li><p>Support change, patching, and upgrade activities for network infrastructure.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with internal teams and vendors to resolve complex network issues.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate network documentation and configuration records.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>4 years of hands-on experience</strong> in configuring and supporting routers and switches (e.g., Cisco).</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of networking fundamentals (LAN/WAN, TCP/IP, VLANs, routing protocols).</p></li><li><p><strong>CCNA certification (mandatory)</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience with network security concepts and best practices.</p></li><li><p>Good troubleshooting, communication, and documentation skills.</p></li></ul>",
